<subSubSection id="C31E6567FFCAF62481163F58F94EF282" pageId="14" pageNumber="72" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BBB36ECFFCAF62481163F58F797F42F" blockId="14.[2056,2650,2884,3311]" pageId="14" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B970EAFEFFCAF62481163F58F706F4FE" bold="true" box="[2056,2211,2884,2917]" pageId="14" pageNumber="72">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C044D6FFFCAF62481A93F58F7E8F417" authority="Thomas, 1893" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1893" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Cynopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="72" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maculatus">Cynopterus maculatus Thomas, 1893</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B6C3CB1FFCAF624817D3F77F797F42F" pageId="14" pageNumber="72">
“ 
<collectingCountry id="F313767CFFCAF624816E3F77F746F417" box="[2160,2275,2923,2956]" name="Malaysia" pageId="14" pageNumber="72">Sarawak</collectingCountry>
,” western Borneo, 
<collectingCountry id="F313767CFFCAF624831F3F77F78BF42F" name="Malaysia" pageId="14" pageNumber="72">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBB36ECFFCAF62481163FA6F94EF282" blockId="14.[2056,2650,2884,3311]" lastBlockId="14.[1444,2650,3320,3470]" pageId="14" pageNumber="72">
The two traditionally recognized subspecies, type 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D6FFFCAF624818F3FFDF6A2F399" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[2193,2311,3041,3074]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Balionycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="72" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maculata">maculata</taxonomicName>
in Borneo (slightly larger and browner but otherwise very much alike) and sesmundi in Peninsular 
<collectingCountry id="F313767CFFCAF624831F382CF78BF3E2" name="Malaysia" pageId="14" pageNumber="72">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, have 12% genetic divergence (using cytochrome-b sequences) that warrants species-level recognition. 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D6FFFCAF624809438BBF597F353" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[2442,2610,3239,3272]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Balionycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="72" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maculata">B. maculata</taxonomicName>
is also distinguished morphometrically from B. setmundi. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31E6567FFCAF6248CBA3903F96AF2DB" box="[1444,1743,3359,3392]" pageId="14" pageNumber="72" type="distribution">
<caption id="DF7B6664FFCAF6248CBA3903F96AF2DB" box="[1444,1743,3359,3392]" inLine="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="72" targetBox="[980,984,2257,2282]" targetPageId="15">
